shares her favorite martini to get you in the holiday mood, The Normandie Club Number 1.

Ingredients to make 1 serving:
2 oz Absolut Elyx

shared by @jeffrey_m_muller from @bespokebarla, the Åhus Glögg.

To make 10 servings to enjoy with your friends first prepare the homemade Winter Spiced Syrup, which you can keep in your fridge and use all season for delicious cocktails.

Winter Spiced Syrup (makes just over 1L).
1kg Superfine/caster sugar
1L Water
50g Chopped Fresh Ginger Root
50g Mixed Dried Fruits (raisin, sultana, apricot, figs)
20 Fresh Orange Zests
10 Green Cardamom Pods
5 Cloves
2 Cinnamon Sticks
20g Citric Acid.

Measure ingredients in to saucepan and bring to the boil to ensure all sugar is melted. Heat together for 10-15 minutes. Remove from heat and let syrup cool with ingredients still infusing. When syrup is cold strain into an empty bottle and keep in your fridge.

Åhus Glögg 
5 oz Absolut Elyx
1 Bottle Red Wine 
2 oz Pedro Ximenez Sherry
5 oz Homemade Winter Spice Syrup

Combine red wine, Elyx and Winter Spice syrup in a saucepan, stir and warm gently until simmering. Add sherry and stir and serve in a handled cup. Garnish with toasted almonds and sultanas. Skål!

ALL HALLOWS

15 ml Lemon Juice

with @nickstrangeway, seminal London bartender and mixologist extraordinaire.

Martini Royale

2 parts Absolut Elyx
½ part Lillet Blanc
½ part Fino Sherry
½ part Blackcurrant Cordial
2 parts Rosé Sparkling Wine

Fill a Copper Balloon cup full of ice, add all ingredients in the order shown, then top with sparkling wine and stir gently to combine.
Garnish with a squeeze of grapefruit and lemon peels, along with sprigs of thyme and mint, then serve.

#AbsolutElyx #CockailsAndPajamas #CopperMakesItBetter
